The divine is found only in extremes: in the childlike holy fool and the wise elder, in caring about nothing in the world or caring about every single blade of grass in it, in the newborn and in the dying man. There is never contradiction between complete opposites.

Mister Lukanov, abysmally drunk, often exited the house and screamed "Fuck your mothers, communists. Fuck your mothers, f******!"

The tiny landlord lady, lost her mind decades ago, went out on the balconry and excitedly applauded him: "Bravo!" - she screamed - "What a good man!"

The old woman, of course, had no idea who or what the communists were. Often, after midnight, she wandered around the apartment and asked loudly who lived there. The place was swarming with cockroaches - millions.
Democracy dies in darkness (my bowels). I shit pure totalitarianism.

I have read two versions of the explanation how dogs came to be. One is basically summed up as "wolves with autism" and the other as "wolves with the autism bred away from them". Both hold great theological implications.

One time I read about a family that bought a house on top of a hill that was infested with snakes. At night they stayed up and listened to them slither inside the walls. They were everywhere, thousands. Some nights I feel that the entire world was built on top of a snake hill...

I sense that everything is infested with snakes - buildings, bricks, cars, people - everything that I am unable to see is a nest of snakes. Maybe, right where I am standing, in a parallel dimension there is a serpentine orgy. Death.

All our hearts are magnets that repel each other, but are all attracted to the hells below. Our job on this earth is to force them together, to exhaust them, to pile their corpses into a staircase leading up.
It's time to start training your grip strength
Humanize yourself and face to tearshed and laughter!
